KwaZulu Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala. JOHANNESBURG - KwaZulu-Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala says he is concerned about big group gatherings, which are adding to coronavirus infections across the province. He is pleading with people to adhere to distancing and other safety measures. READ: KZN economy hit hard by COVID-19 "We plead with everyone to adhere to the regulations. If we can stay safe today then we can be safe and together tomorrow," said Zikalala. KwaZulu-Natal has confirmed over 23 000 cases of COVID-19, with 273 deaths reported so far. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.